you will be like a fish after skinning.

1052
01:14:50,371 --> 01:14:52,661
Your best man fights our best man...

1053
01:14:52,792 --> 01:14:55,496
and er... we pick him.

1054
01:14:55,627 --> 01:14:58,831
- I thought I would be fighting with...
- You shook on it!

1055
01:15:02,843 --> 01:15:04,882
Yes. I shook on it.

1056
01:15:05,011 --> 01:15:07,799
Bernardo,
if you want to change your mind...

1057
01:15:18,149 --> 01:15:22,065
- Bernardo, want a cigarette?
- No, thank you. I don't smoke.

1058
01:15:26,366 --> 01:15:28,407
Evening, Lieutenant.

1059
01:15:28,536 --> 01:15:30,908
I and Tony was just closing up.

1060
01:15:32,373 --> 01:15:35,707
Well! Now, this is more like it, fellas.

1061
01:15:35,835 --> 01:15:38,124
Warms me all over to see you this way.

1062
01:15:38,254 --> 01:15:42,631
And after only a couple of words
from me at the playground today.

1063
01:15:42,759 --> 01:15:44,751
Oh, do you mind?

1064
01:15:44,886 --> 01:15:47,258
I have no mind. I'm the village idiot.

1065
01:15:49,139 --> 01:15:52,889
Headquarters hears about this,
I may even get a promotion.

1066
01:15:53,227 --> 01:15:55,552
Good deal all around, huh, Bernardo?

1067
01:15:56,605 --> 01:15:58,563
I get a promotion...

1068
01:15:58,691 --> 01:16:01,941
you Puerto Ricans get
what you've been itching for.

1069
01:16:02,070 --> 01:16:04,524
Use of the playground,
use of the gym...

1070
01:16:04,656 --> 01:16:06,695
the streets, the candy store.

1071
01:16:07,951 --> 01:16:11,615
So what if they do turn
this town into a stinking pigsty?

1072
01:16:11,745 --> 01:16:14,035
Don't stop him!
He wants to get home...

1073
01:16:14,165 --> 01:16:17,249
write to San Juan,
tell them how he's got it made here.

1074
01:16:18,711 --> 01:16:21,712
What I mean is... clear out, you!

1075
01:16:21,840 --> 01:16:23,002
I said clear out!

1076
01:16:26,845 --> 01:16:28,884
Oh, yeah, sure. I know.

1077
01:16:29,014 --> 01:16:31,765
It's a free country,
and I ain't got the right.

1078
01:16:31,891 --> 01:16:34,133
But I got a badge.

1079
01:16:34,269 --> 01:16:36,475
What have you got?

1080
01:16:36,605 --> 01:16:38,265
Things are tough all over.

1081
01:16:38,398 --> 01:16:39,393
Beat it!

1082
01:17:11,765 --> 01:17:13,805
OK, fellas.

1083
01:17:14,810 --> 01:17:16,848
Where's the rumble gonna be?

1084
01:17:18,230 --> 01:17:19,724
Come on!

1085
01:17:19,857 --> 01:17:22,941
Americans don't rub with
the gold-teeth unless...

1086
01:17:23,068 --> 01:17:25,737
- Look, Lieutenant!
- You shut your mouth.

1087
01:17:28,073 --> 01:17:30,113
Come on, Baby John...

1088
01:17:30,242 --> 01:17:33,362
before your smooth little kisser
gets cut up for life.

1089
01:17:33,495 --> 01:17:35,155
Now, where's it gonna be?

1090
01:17:35,289 --> 01:17:37,328
<i>The river?</i>

1091
01:17:37,458 --> 01:17:38,832
The park?

1092
01:17:42,880 --> 01:17:44,919
Look, fellas! I'm for you!

1093
01:17:45,049 --> 01:17:48,168
I want this beat cleaned up
and you can do it for me.

1094
01:17:48,302 --> 01:17:50,923
I'll even lend a hand
if things get rough.

1095
01:17:51,055 --> 01:17:53,094
Now, where are you gonna rumble?

1096
01:17:55,935 --> 01:17:59,268
The playground?

1097
01:17:59,396 --> 01:18:01,851
Sweeney's lot?

1098
01:18:07,738 --> 01:18:10,739
Why don't you get smart,
you stupid hooligans?

1099
01:18:10,866 --> 01:18:13,820
I ought to throw you
in the can right now!

1100
01:18:13,953 --> 01:18:17,073
You and the tinhorn immigrant scum
you come from!

1101
01:18:18,916 --> 01:18:20,956
How's your old man's DTs, A-rab?

1102
01:18:23,920 --> 01:18:28,049
How's the action on your mother's
side of the street, Action?

1103
01:18:28,926 --> 01:18:31,595
One day,
there won't be anyone to hold you!

1104
01:18:31,721 --> 01:18:33,464
Get him out of here! Come on!

1105
01:18:34,974 --> 01:18:37,891
Don't worry.
I'll find out where it's gonna be.

1106
01:18:38,018 --> 01:18:40,142
Be sure to finish each other off...

1107
01:18:40,271 --> 01:18:42,643
because if you don't, I will.

1108
01:18:51,741 --> 01:18:53,483
Oh, yeah, sure.

1109
01:18:53,617 --> 01:18:55,160
Understand 'em.

1110
01:18:55,286 --> 01:18:59,154
That's what they keep telling me
at headquarters - understand.

1111
01:18:59,290 --> 01:19:03,039
You try keeping hoodlums in line
and see what it does to you.

1112
01:19:06,089 --> 01:19:09,789
It wouldn't give me a mouth like his.

1113
01:19:14,097 --> 01:19:17,133
Come on, Doc. Don't let it get you.

1114
01:19:17,267 --> 01:19:19,094
I'm sick.

1115
01:19:19,227 --> 01:19:21,469
You heard. It's gonna be a fair fight.

1116
01:19:21,604 --> 01:19:23,562
And that's gonna cure something?

1117
01:19:23,690 --> 01:19:27,141
From here on in,
everything's gonna be all right.

1118
01:19:27,277 --> 01:19:30,480
- I got a feeling.
- What have you been taking tonight?

1119
01:19:30,613 --> 01:19:32,440
A trip to the moon.

1120
01:19:32,574 --> 01:19:34,401
And I tell you a secret, Doc.

1121
01:19:34,534 --> 01:19:36,408
It ain't a man that's up there.

1122
01:19:36,536 --> 01:19:38,576
It's a girl.

1123
01:19:38,705 --> 01:19:40,662
A lady.

1124
01:19:42,542 --> 01:19:44,166
Buenas noches, señor.

1125
01:19:44,293 --> 01:19:46,334
Buenas noches.

1126
01:19:47,380 --> 01:19:49,753
So that's why you made it
a fair fight?

1127
01:19:49,883 --> 01:19:51,839
I'm seeing her tomorrow. I can't wait.

1128
01:19:51,967 --> 01:19:53,083
Tony!

1129
01:19:53,220 --> 01:19:55,212
Things aren't tough enough?

1130
01:19:55,347 --> 01:19:57,339
Tough? Doc, I'm in love.

1131
01:19:57,474 --> 01:20:00,143
- And you're not frightened?
- Should I be?

1132
01:20:01,478 --> 01:20:03,056
No.

1133
01:20:03,188 --> 01:20:06,106
No, I'm frightened enough
for the both of you.

1134
01:20:09,945 --> 01:20:11,984
<i>♪ "Maria" ♪</i>

1135
01:20:53,030 --> 01:20:55,070
<i>♪ "I Feel Pretty" ♪</i>

1136
01:21:08,045 --> 01:21:10,085
What has Chino done to her?

1137
01:21:10,214 --> 01:21:12,254
Chino? Why Chino?

1138
01:21:12,383 --> 01:21:14,589
Maybe she is just dolling up for us.

1139
01:21:14,760 --> 01:21:16,753
Gracias, querida.

1140
01:21:16,887 --> 01:21:19,888
Rosalia, Consuelo,
my adorable friends.

1141
01:21:20,057 --> 01:21:21,468
Can you keep a secret?

1142
01:21:21,600 --> 01:21:23,640
I'm hot for secrets!

1143
01:21:25,146 --> 01:21:27,185
No, I won't tell you.

1144
01:21:27,315 --> 01:21:29,141
- What?
- What?

1145
01:21:29,275 --> 01:21:31,102
The poor girl is out of her mind!

1146
01:21:31,235 --> 01:21:32,860
I am. Crazy!

1147
01:21:32,987 --> 01:21:36,190
She might be at that.
She looks somehow different.

1148
01:21:36,324 --> 01:21:38,897
- I do?
- And I think she is up to something.

1149
01:21:39,035 --> 01:21:40,695
I am?

1150
01:21:40,828 --> 01:21:43,498
"I do?" "I am?" She talks like a parrot.

1151
01:21:43,623 --> 01:21:45,781
What is going on with you, Maria?

1152
01:21:45,917 --> 01:21:47,292
♪ I feel pretty ♪

1153
01:21:47,418 --> 01:21:48,877
♪ Oh, so pretty ♪

1154
01:21:49,003 --> 01:21:52,206
♪ I feel pretty and witty and gay ♪

1155
01:21:52,340 --> 01:21:56,551
♪ And I pity any girl who isn't me today ♪

1156
01:21:58,554 --> 01:21:59,883
♪ I feel charming ♪

1157
01:22:00,014 --> 01:22:01,425
♪ Oh, so charming ♪

1158
01:22:01,557 --> 01:22:04,842
♪ It's alarming how charming I feel ♪

1159
01:22:04,978 --> 01:22:06,306
♪ And so pretty ♪

1160
01:22:06,437 --> 01:22:08,644
♪ That I hardly can believe I'm real ♪

1161
01:22:11,651 --> 01:22:14,486
♪ See the pretty girl
in that mirror there ♪

1162
01:22:15,321 --> 01:22:18,156
♪ Who can that attractive girl be? ♪

1163
01:22:18,283 --> 01:22:19,741
♪ Such a pretty face,
such a pretty dress ♪

1164
01:22:19,868 --> 01:22:22,323
♪ Such a pretty smile,
such a pretty me ♪

1165
01:22:23,830 --> 01:22:25,158
♪ I feel stunning ♪

1166
01:22:25,290 --> 01:22:26,665
♪ And entrancing ♪

1167
01:22:26,791 --> 01:22:30,207
♪ Feel like running and dancing for joy ♪

1168
01:22:30,670 --> 01:22:31,749
♪ For I'm loved ♪

1169
01:22:31,880 --> 01:22:35,877
♪ By a pretty wonderful boy ♪

1170
01:22:40,055 --> 01:22:42,972
♪ Have you met my good friend Maria? ♪

1171
01:22:43,099 --> 01:22:45,637
♪ The craziest girl on the block ♪

1172
01:22:46,478 --> 01:22:48,933
♪ You'll know her the
minute you see her ♪

1173
01:22:49,065 --> 01:22:52,729
♪ She's the one who is in
an advanced state of shock ♪

1174
01:22:52,859 --> 01:22:54,270
♪ She thinks she's in love ♪

1175
01:22:54,402 --> 01:22:56,691
- ♪ She thinks she's in Spain ♪
- ♪ La la la ♪

1176
01:22:56,822 --> 01:23:00,107
♪ She isn't in love,
she's merely insane ♪

1177
01:23:00,951 --> 01:23:02,279
♪ It must be the heat ♪

1178
01:23:02,411 --> 01:23:04,450
- ♪ Or some rare disease ♪
- ♪ La la la ♪

1179
01:23:04,579 --> 01:23:06,371
♪ Or too much to eat ♪

1180
01:23:06,498 --> 01:23:09,036
♪ Or maybe it's fleas ♪

1181
01:23:09,167 --> 01:23:10,959
♪ Keep away from her ♪

1182
01:23:11,087 --> 01:23:12,497
♪ Send for Chino ♪

1183
01:23:12,629 --> 01:23:15,749
♪ This is not the Maria we know ♪

1184
01:23:15,882 --> 01:23:17,293
♪ Modest and pure ♪

1185
01:23:17,426 --> 01:23:19,335
- ♪ Polite and refined ♪
- ♪ La la la ♪

1186
01:23:19,469 --> 01:23:20,714
♪ Well bred and mature ♪

1187
01:23:20,846 --> 01:23:23,800
♪ And out of her mind! ♪

1188
01:23:23,932 --> 01:23:26,257
Miss America!

1189
01:23:26,393 --> 01:23:28,433
Ay, qué linda que eres!

1190
01:23:28,562 --> 01:23:30,970
Miss America! Bravo! Speech!

1191
01:23:31,106 --> 01:23:32,766
Speech!

1192
01:23:32,900 --> 01:23:34,180
♪ I feel pretty ♪

1193
01:23:34,318 --> 01:23:35,776
♪ Oh, so pretty ♪

1194
01:23:35,903 --> 01:23:39,272
♪ That the city
should give me its key ♪

1195
01:23:39,406 --> 01:23:43,570
♪ A committee should be
organised to honour me ♪

1196
01:23:43,702 --> 01:23:45,362
♪ La la la la la la la-la ♪

1197
01:23:45,496 --> 01:23:47,073
♪ I feel dizzy ♪

1198
01:23:47,206 --> 01:23:48,486
♪ I feel sunny ♪

1199
01:23:48,624 --> 01:23:51,874
♪ I feel fizzy and funny and fine ♪

1200
01:23:52,002 --> 01:23:53,378
♪ And so pretty ♪

1201
01:23:53,504 --> 01:23:55,995
♪ Miss America can just resign ♪

1202
01:23:56,131 --> 01:23:58,373
♪ La la la la la la la-la ♪

1203
01:23:58,509 --> 01:24:01,593
♪ See the pretty girl
in that mirror there ♪

1204
01:24:01,720 --> 01:24:02,753
♪ What mirror where? ♪

1205
01:24:02,889 --> 01:24:04,632
♪ Who can that attractive girl be? ♪

1206
01:24:04,765 --> 01:24:05,963
- ♪ Which? What? ♪
- ♪ Where? Whom? ♪

1207
01:24:06,100 --> 01:24:07,642
♪ Such a pretty face,
such a pretty dress ♪

1208
01:24:07,768 --> 01:24:09,512
♪ Such a pretty smile,
such a pretty me ♪

1209
01:24:09,645 --> 01:24:11,554
- ♪ Such a pretty me ♪
- ♪ Such a pretty me ♪

1210
01:24:11,689 --> 01:24:13,516
- ♪ I feel stunning ♪
- ♪ I feel stunning ♪

1211
01:24:13,649 --> 01:24:15,227
- ♪ And entrancing ♪
- ♪ And entrancing ♪

1212
01:24:15,359 --> 01:24:17,816
♪ Feel like running and dancing for joy ♪

1213
01:24:17,945 --> 01:24:24,529
♪ For I'm loved by a
pretty wonderful boy ♪

1214
01:24:29,707 --> 01:24:31,746
Cállense, por favor, muchachas!

1215
01:24:31,876 --> 01:24:34,201
You want to sing,
do it with the needles...

1216
01:24:34,337 --> 01:24:36,709
or you'll be singing for your supper.

1217
01:24:36,839 --> 01:24:40,089
What can you expect?
We use Singer sewing machines.

1218
01:24:40,218 --> 01:24:43,587
Sure. You make the bad joke
at home where I can't hear it.

1219
01:24:43,721 --> 01:24:46,294
Go now, go home.
It's closing time. Shoo!

1220
01:24:46,432 --> 01:24:48,259
Buenas noches, Madam Lucia!

1221
01:24:48,392 --> 01:24:51,097
You pull down the shades,
pick up the pins...

1222
01:24:51,229 --> 01:24:53,933
turn off the lights
and lock the doors.

1223
01:24:54,066 --> 01:24:56,638
Buenas noches, Anita.

1224
01:24:56,776 --> 01:24:57,772
Buenas noches.

1225
01:24:59,612 --> 01:25:01,736
Ay, the jail is open!

1226
01:25:01,865 --> 01:25:03,857
I thought she'd never leave.

1227
01:25:03,992 --> 01:25:07,610
It's hard to believe that old bag
was once a young bag like us.

1228
01:25:07,745 --> 01:25:10,782
Let's go before she changes her mind
and comes back.

1229
01:25:10,915 --> 01:25:13,702
You go, querida. I will lock up.

1230
01:25:13,835 --> 01:25:15,874
- Why?
- I have work.

1231
01:25:16,004 --> 01:25:19,337
- Do it tomorrow.
- I am in no hurry.

1232
01:25:19,465 --> 01:25:23,796
I am. I'm going home now
and take a nice long bubble bath.

1233
01:25:23,929 --> 01:25:25,470
Black orchid.

1234
01:25:25,597 --> 01:25:27,305
Black orchid?

1235
01:25:27,432 --> 01:25:29,471
Mm. All over.

1236
01:25:29,601 --> 01:25:31,844
I got a date with Nardo after the rumble.

1237
01:25:31,978 --> 01:25:34,101
What rumble?

1238
01:25:34,230 --> 01:25:36,437
Oh. Well, er...

1239
01:25:36,566 --> 01:25:39,188
Nardo's Sharks
and those boys at the dance.

1240
01:25:40,362 --> 01:25:42,319
<i>They fight each other tonight?</i>

1241
01:25:42,447 --> 01:25:44,487
They don't play potsy.

1242
01:25:46,535 --> 01:25:48,574
Why must they always fight?

1243
01:25:48,703 --> 01:25:50,281
You saw how they dance...

1244
01:25:50,413 --> 01:25:52,952
like they gotta get rid of something.

1245
01:25:53,084 --> 01:25:54,660
That's how they fight.

1246
01:25:54,793 --> 01:25:56,832
To get rid of what?

1247
01:25:57,295 --> 01:25:59,335
Too much feeling.

1248
01:25:59,464 --> 01:26:01,173
And they do get rid of it.

1249
01:26:01,300 --> 01:26:04,834
Boy, after a fight,
that brother of yours is so healthy.

1250
01:26:04,970 --> 01:26:07,758
Definitely. Black orchid.

1251
01:26:18,775 --> 01:26:20,104
Buenas noches.

1252
01:26:22,405 --> 01:26:25,321
"You go, querida. I will lock up."

1253
01:26:28,285 --> 01:26:30,113
It's too early for noches.

1254
01:26:30,246 --> 01:26:32,285
Buenas tardes.

1255
01:26:32,414 --> 01:26:34,454
Gracias.

1256
01:26:34,583 --> 01:26:36,410
Buenas tardes.

1257
01:26:36,543 --> 01:26:39,829
He just came from the drugstore
to deliver aspirin.

1258
01:26:39,963 --> 01:26:42,454
- You'll need it.
- Not us.

1259
01:26:42,591 --> 01:26:45,379
We're fine. We're out of the world.

1260
01:26:45,512 --> 01:26:47,669
You're out of your heads.

1261
01:26:47,805 --> 01:26:49,714
We're 12 feet in the air.

1262
01:26:49,848 --> 01:26:51,889
Anita can see that.

1263
01:26:56,313 --> 01:26:58,353
You will not tell?

1264
01:27:00,568 --> 01:27:02,607
Tell what?

1265
01:27:02,736 --> 01:27:05,654
How can I know
what goes on 12 feet over my head?

1266
01:27:07,826 --> 01:27:11,241
You'd better be home in 15 minutes.

1267
01:27:19,712 --> 01:27:21,752
It's all right. She likes us.

1268
01:27:22,716 --> 01:27:25,253
But she is worried... and so am I.

1269
01:27:25,384 --> 01:27:28,421
- That's foolish.
- Are you going to the rumble?

1270
01:27:28,555 --> 01:27:30,594
- No!
- Yes.

1271
01:27:30,723 --> 01:27:31,719
Why?

1272
01:27:31,849 --> 01:27:34,422
- You must go and stop it.
- I have stopped it.

1273
01:27:34,560 --> 01:27:36,850
It'll only be a fist fight between two.

1274
01:27:36,980 --> 01:27:38,604
Any fight is no good for us!

1275
01:27:38,731 --> 01:27:41,269
Everything is good for us.
We've got magic.

1276
01:27:41,400 --> 01:27:43,441
Listen, and hear me.

1277
01:27:43,987 --> 01:27:46,062
You must go and stop it.

1278
01:27:47,406 --> 01:27:49,446
It means that much to you?

1279
01:27:49,575 --> 01:27:50,905
Yes.

1280
01:27:51,036 --> 01:27:52,695
All right, I will.

1281
01:27:53,746 --> 01:27:57,281
I believe you. You do have magic.

1282
01:27:57,416 --> 01:27:59,457
Of course.

1283
01:27:59,586 --> 01:28:01,128
I've got you.

1284
01:28:03,756 --> 01:28:06,544
Tonight, after I stop the rumble,
I'll come by for you.

1285
01:28:06,677 --> 01:28:08,715
I will wait for you on the roof.

1286
01:28:08,845 --> 01:28:11,051
No. Not the roof.

1287
01:28:11,180 --> 01:28:12,759
I'll come to your house.

1288
01:28:13,976 --> 01:28:16,347
You cannot. My mama...

1289
01:28:17,520 --> 01:28:19,560
Then, I'll take you to my house.

1290
01:28:19,689 --> 01:28:21,350
<i>Your mama? ♪</i>

1291
01:28:23,067 --> 01:28:26,271
She'll come running
from the kitchen to welcome you.

1292
01:28:26,404 --> 01:28:27,947
She lives in the kitchen.

1293
01:28:28,073 --> 01:28:30,148
Dressed so elegant?

1294
01:28:30,283 --> 01:28:31,861
I told her you were coming.

1295
01:28:31,993 --> 01:28:34,484
She'll look at your face -
try not to smile.

1296
01:28:34,621 --> 01:28:36,993
She'll say, "Skinny... but pretty!"

1297
01:28:38,083 --> 01:28:39,790
She is plump, no doubt?

1298
01:28:40,585 --> 01:28:41,913
Fat.

1299
01:28:42,046 --> 01:28:45,580
I take after my mama. Delicate-boned.

1300
01:28:45,715 --> 01:28:47,423
Oh!

