02:10:23,739 --> 02:10:25,564
Doc will know.

1817
02:10:25,698 --> 02:10:27,821
Tell him I have been detained...

1818
02:10:27,950 --> 02:10:29,825
and can't get there right away.

1819
02:10:31,288 --> 02:10:33,576
Or I would have picked it up myself.

1820
02:10:44,217 --> 02:10:46,044
Excuse me.

1821
02:10:46,178 --> 02:10:48,253
You were asking?

1822
02:10:48,387 --> 02:10:50,261
Yeah.

1823
02:10:50,389 --> 02:10:53,226
At the gym,
your brother got into an argument...

1824
02:10:53,352 --> 02:10:55,806
because you danced with the wrong boy.

1825
02:10:58,231 --> 02:11:00,271
Yes.

1826
02:11:00,401 --> 02:11:02,439
Who was the boy?

1827
02:11:02,568 --> 02:11:04,608
Another from my country.

1828
02:11:05,697 --> 02:11:07,737
And his name?

1829
02:11:07,866 --> 02:11:09,147
José.

1830
02:11:19,043 --> 02:11:21,417
- Can't find him.
- Down in the cellar.

1831
02:11:21,547 --> 02:11:23,006
- Tony?
- Safe and sound.

1832
02:11:23,132 --> 02:11:25,752
- I found him.
- Did you warn him about Chino?

1833
02:11:25,884 --> 02:11:28,755
- Why's he in the cellar?
- To keep the mice company.

1834
02:11:28,888 --> 02:11:30,596
No sign of Chino, huh?

1835
02:11:30,723 --> 02:11:32,761
- Nothing.
- His luck.

1836
02:11:32,891 --> 02:11:35,761
I'll slip out the back
and check the alleys again.

1837
02:11:35,895 --> 02:11:37,437
- You guys, hang here.
- OK.

1838
02:11:37,563 --> 02:11:39,353
Boy, I'm thirsty. Where's Doc?

1839
02:11:39,481 --> 02:11:42,019
Upstairs,
raising getaway money for Tony.

1840
02:11:42,150 --> 02:11:44,724
- Doc ain't got no money.
- His mattress has.

1841
02:11:44,862 --> 02:11:47,945
Cut the frabbajabba.
Grab some reading matter.

1842
02:11:48,073 --> 02:11:49,733
Some of you get outside.

1843
02:11:49,866 --> 02:11:52,536
If you see Chino, or those stinking PRs...

1844
02:12:03,046 --> 02:12:04,671
I'd like to see Doc.

1845
02:12:04,798 --> 02:12:06,590
He ain't here.

1846
02:12:06,717 --> 02:12:08,212
Where is he?

1847
02:12:08,344 --> 02:12:11,048
At the bank. They made
a mistake in his favour.

1848
02:12:11,179 --> 02:12:14,217
The banks are closed at night.
Where is he?

1849
02:12:14,350 --> 02:12:16,141
You know how skinny Doc is.

1850
02:12:16,268 --> 02:12:18,593
He slipped through
the night deposit slot.

1851
02:12:18,729 --> 02:12:20,556
And got stuck, halfway in.

1852
02:12:20,690 --> 02:12:23,263
So there's no telling when he'll be back.

1853
02:12:25,986 --> 02:12:28,692
Buenas noches, señorita.

1854
02:12:37,415 --> 02:12:39,039
Where are you going?

1855
02:12:39,166 --> 02:12:41,205
Downstairs.

1856
02:12:41,335 --> 02:12:43,375
Didn't I tell you? He ain't here.

1857
02:12:43,505 --> 02:12:45,627
I'd like to see for myself.

1858
02:12:48,592 --> 02:12:51,049
Please.

1859
02:12:53,305 --> 02:12:56,140
Please.

1860
02:12:57,018 --> 02:12:59,058
Por favor.

1861
02:12:59,187 --> 02:13:00,977
Will you let me pass?

1862
02:13:01,105 --> 02:13:02,978
She's too dark to pass.

1863
02:13:03,107 --> 02:13:04,935
<i>- Oh, don't.
- Please don't.</i>

1864
02:13:05,068 --> 02:13:06,313
Por favor!

1865
02:13:06,444 --> 02:13:07,854
- Gracias!
- De nada!

1866
02:13:07,987 --> 02:13:10,110
- Ay, ay! Hey, mambo!
- Listen, you!

1867
02:13:10,239 --> 02:13:12,992
Look, I gotta give
a friend of yours a message.

1868
02:13:13,118 --> 02:13:14,529
I gotta tell Tony...

1869
02:13:14,661 --> 02:13:17,032
- He ain't here.
- I know he is.

1870
02:13:17,163 --> 02:13:19,489
- Who's the message from?
- Never mind.

1871
02:13:19,624 --> 02:13:21,119
Could it be from Chino?

1872
02:13:21,251 --> 02:13:24,370
Don't you understand? I want to help.

1873
02:13:24,503 --> 02:13:26,544
Bernardo's girl wants to help?

1874
02:13:26,673 --> 02:13:28,796
Even a greaseball's got feelings.

1875
02:13:28,925 --> 02:13:30,798
- She wants to help get Tony.
- No!

1876
02:13:30,926 --> 02:13:32,504
Not much! Bernardo's tramp.

1877
02:13:32,636 --> 02:13:35,259
- Bernardo's pig.
- You lying Spic!

1878
02:13:35,390 --> 02:13:37,217
- Don't do that!
- Gold-tooth!

1879
02:13:37,351 --> 02:13:39,757
- Pierced ear!
- Garlic mouth!

1880
02:13:39,894 --> 02:13:41,223
Cha! Cha-cha!

1881
02:13:41,355 --> 02:13:43,478
Cha-cha-cha!

1882
02:13:47,318 --> 02:13:49,146
Olé! Olé!

1883
02:14:03,627 --> 02:14:05,667
<i>♪ "America" ♪</i>

1884
02:14:15,471 --> 02:14:17,511
<i>Stop it!</i>

1885
02:14:21,936 --> 02:14:24,261
What are you doing there?

1886
02:14:43,209 --> 02:14:45,247
Bernardo was right.

1887
02:14:47,171 --> 02:14:48,998
If one of you...

1888
02:14:49,131 --> 02:14:52,582
was lying in the street bleeding...

1889
02:14:52,717 --> 02:14:54,960
I'd walk by and spit on you.

1890
02:14:55,096 --> 02:14:57,717
Stop her!
She'll tell Chino Tony's in the cellar.

1891
02:14:57,848 --> 02:14:59,258
Don't you touch me.

1892
02:15:02,812 --> 02:15:05,682
I got a message for your American buddy.

1893
02:15:06,565 --> 02:15:10,433
You tell that murderer
that Maria's never going to meet him.

1894
02:15:11,779 --> 02:15:14,565
You tell him
Chino found out about them...

1895
02:15:14,698 --> 02:15:16,738
and shot her!

1896
02:15:17,910 --> 02:15:19,950
She's dead!

1897
02:15:24,292 --> 02:15:26,331
When do you kids stop?

1898
02:15:27,003 --> 02:15:30,169
You make this world lousy.

1899
02:15:31,173 --> 02:15:33,213
We didn't make it, Doc.

1900
02:15:34,719 --> 02:15:36,758
Get out of here.

1901
02:16:07,042 --> 02:16:08,870
Maria?

1902
02:16:09,170 --> 02:16:11,377
Doc, I though I heard... You got it!

1903
02:16:11,506 --> 02:16:13,545
Yeah, I got it.

1904
02:16:14,341 --> 02:16:17,592
You're a pal.
You're the best friend a guy ever had.

1905
02:16:17,721 --> 02:16:20,471
I'll pay you back as soon as I can,
I promise.

1906
02:16:20,598 --> 02:16:22,805
- Forget that.
- Never! I couldn't.

1907
02:16:22,934 --> 02:16:25,935
You know what we're gonna do
in the country, Maria and me?

1908
02:16:26,062 --> 02:16:29,146
We're gonna have lots of kids.
We'll name 'em all after you.

1909
02:16:29,273 --> 02:16:31,231
So when you come to visit...

1910
02:16:31,359 --> 02:16:32,735
Wake up!

1911
02:16:33,737 --> 02:16:36,309
Is this the only way
to get through to you?

1912
02:16:36,447 --> 02:16:39,484
Do just what you all do?

1913
02:16:39,618 --> 02:16:41,492
Bust like a hot water pipe?

1914
02:16:41,620 --> 02:16:43,030
What's got into you?

1915
02:16:43,162 --> 02:16:46,330
Why do you kids live
like there's a war on?

1916
02:16:51,254 --> 02:16:53,294
Why do you kill?

1917
02:16:57,094 --> 02:16:59,132
I told you how it happened.

1918
02:16:59,596 --> 02:17:01,838
Maria understands.

1919
02:17:02,724 --> 02:17:04,763
I thought you did too.

1920
02:17:04,892 --> 02:17:06,850
Maria understands nothing...

1921
02:17:06,979 --> 02:17:09,018
ever again.

1922
02:17:09,148 --> 02:17:11,187
There is no Maria, Tony.

1923
02:17:15,654 --> 02:17:16,603
What?

1924
02:17:17,823 --> 02:17:19,364
I can't.

1925
02:17:19,490 --> 02:17:20,486
No, no, Doc.

1926
02:17:21,492 --> 02:17:23,652
Now, tell me. What is it?

1927
02:17:24,788 --> 02:17:26,946
That was Anita upstairs.

1928
02:17:28,166 --> 02:17:30,622
Chino found out about you and Maria...

1929
02:17:30,753 --> 02:17:33,326
and he killed her.

1930
02:17:41,013 --> 02:17:42,839
No...

1931
02:17:48,604 --> 02:17:50,643
Maria.

1932
02:17:57,195 --> 02:17:59,236
Maria died?

1933
02:18:08,708 --> 02:18:09,703
Chino!

1934
02:18:10,334 --> 02:18:11,329
Chino!

1935
02:18:13,754 --> 02:18:16,080
Come and get me too, Chino!

1936
02:18:18,884 --> 02:18:20,924
Chino!

1937
02:18:23,473 --> 02:18:24,468
Chino!

1938
02:18:28,269 --> 02:18:30,309
Chino!

1939
02:18:30,438 --> 02:18:32,265
Come and get me too, Chino!

1940
02:18:32,398 --> 02:18:33,726
- Tony!
- Who's that?

1941
02:18:33,857 --> 02:18:36,693
- Anybodys. Come on!
- Get out of here.

1942
02:18:36,819 --> 02:18:38,195
Chino!

1943
02:18:38,321 --> 02:18:41,025
- Come and get me, damn you!
- What are you doing?

1944
02:18:41,156 --> 02:18:42,152
Get out of here!

1945
02:18:42,282 --> 02:18:44,323
- Chino!
- Come with me...

1946
02:18:44,452 --> 02:18:47,370
It ain't playing any more.
Can't anyone get that?

1947
02:18:47,497 --> 02:18:49,370
- But the gang!
- You're a girl!

1948
02:18:49,498 --> 02:18:51,207
Be a girl and beat it!

1949
02:18:55,338 --> 02:18:56,333
Chino!

1950
02:18:57,966 --> 02:18:59,875
Come on, Chino!

1951
02:19:00,009 --> 02:19:01,468
Get me too!

1952
02:19:01,594 --> 02:19:03,633
Chino!

1953
02:19:10,352 --> 02:19:12,393
Chino!

1954
02:19:15,191 --> 02:19:17,517
Chino! I'm calling for you, Chino.

1955
02:19:18,902 --> 02:19:20,980
There's nobody here but me.

1956
02:19:21,114 --> 02:19:23,154
Come on!

1957
02:19:23,283 --> 02:19:25,321
Please, will you?

1958
02:19:25,451 --> 02:19:27,824
I'm waiting for you.

1959
02:19:29,748 --> 02:19:32,073
I want you to.

1960
02:19:41,259 --> 02:19:43,299
Maria!

1961
02:19:44,346 --> 02:19:45,757
Tony!

1962
02:19:48,432 --> 02:19:49,382
Maria!

1963
02:19:55,564 --> 02:19:56,764
Maria!

1964
02:19:59,152 --> 02:20:00,232
Maria!

1965
02:20:27,473 --> 02:20:29,964
I... didn't believe hard enough.

1966
02:20:30,100 --> 02:20:32,139
Loving is enough.

1967
02:20:32,268 --> 02:20:34,677
Not here.

1968
02:20:34,813 --> 02:20:36,853
They won't let us be.

1969
02:20:37,816 --> 02:20:40,058
Then, we'll get away.

1970
02:20:43,322 --> 02:20:45,943
- Yeah. We can.
- Yes.

1971
02:20:46,075 --> 02:20:48,317
- We will.
- Yes.

1972
02:20:49,620 --> 02:20:53,867
♪ Hold my hand and we're halfway there ♪

1973
02:20:56,794 --> 02:21:02,797
♪ Hold my hand and I'll take you there ♪

1974
02:21:03,592 --> 02:21:05,336
♪ Somehow ♪

1975
02:21:05,469 --> 02:21:07,509
♪ Someday ♪

1976
02:21:08,389 --> 02:21:10,927
♪ Some... ♪

1977
02:21:50,598 --> 02:21:52,425
Stay back!

1978
02:22:13,455 --> 02:22:15,696
How do you fire this gun, Chino?

1979
02:22:15,832 --> 02:22:18,074
Just by pulling this little trigger?

1980
02:22:19,836 --> 02:22:21,959
How many bullets are left, Chino?

1981
02:22:23,214 --> 02:22:24,874
Enough for you?

1982
02:22:25,008 --> 02:22:27,047
And you?

1983
02:22:27,177 --> 02:22:28,968
All of you!

1984
02:22:29,095 --> 02:22:30,803
You all killed him!

1985
02:22:30,931 --> 02:22:33,303
And my brother. And Riff.

1986
02:22:33,433 --> 02:22:35,971
Not with bullets and guns.

1987
02:22:36,102 --> 02:22:38,225
With hate.

1988
02:22:38,355 --> 02:22:40,513
Well, I can kill too...

1989
02:22:40,649 --> 02:22:42,641
because now I have hate.

1990
02:22:42,776 --> 02:22:44,685
How many can I kill, Chino?

1991
02:22:44,820 --> 02:22:46,528
How many?

1992
02:22:46,655 --> 02:22:49,027
And still have one bullet left for me?

1993
02:23:10,804 --> 02:23:12,844
Don't you touch him!

1994
02:24:07,737 --> 02:24:09,776
Te adoro, Anton.

1995
02:24:32,345 --> 02:24:34,384
<i>♪ "Somewhere" ♪</i>
